column11:
  In this paper, we generalize several Berezin number inequalities involving
product of operators. For instance, we show that if $A, B$ are positive
operators and $X$ is any operator, then \begin{align*}
\textbf{ber}^{r}(H_{\alpha}(A,B))&\leq\frac{\|X\|^{r}}{2}\textbf{ber}(A^{r}+B^{r})&\leq\frac{\|X\|^{r}}{2}\textbf{ber}(\alpha
A^{r}+(1-\alpha)B^{r})+\textbf{ber}((1-\alpha)A^{r}+\alpha B^{r}), \end{align*}
where $H_{\alpha}(A,B)=\frac{A^\alpha XB^{1-\alpha}+A^{1-\alpha}
XB^{\alpha}}{2}$, $0\leq\alpha\leq1$ and $r\geq2$.
